xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>3739</fr:anchor><fr:addr>jms-00MB</fr:addr><fr:route>jms-00MB.xml</fr:route><fr:title>Quotients and <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00M8.xml"
addr="jms-00M8"
title="Surjection">surjections</fr:link></fr:title><fr:taxon>Example</fr:taxon><fr:date><fr:year>2024</fr:year><fr:month>1</fr:month><fr:day>29</fr:day></fr:date><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link
type="local"
href="jonmsterling.xml"
addr="jonmsterling"
title="Jon Sterling">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author><fr:contributor><fr:link
type="local"
href="marcelofiore.xml"
addr="marcelofiore"
title="Marcelo Fiore">Marcelo Fiore</fr:link></fr:contributor></fr:authors></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>Let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[E]]></fr:tex> be an <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00L4.xml"
addr="jms-00L4"
title="Equivalence relation">equivalence relation</fr:link> on a set <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex>, and let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[q\colon  A\to  A/E]]></fr:tex> be the <fr:em>quotient function</fr:em> that sends <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[a\in  A]]></fr:tex> to its equivalence class <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left  [a\right  ]\mathclose {}}_{E}]]></fr:tex>. Then <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[q\colon  A\to  A/E]]></fr:tex> is <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00M8.xml"
addr="jms-00M8"
title="Surjection">surjective</fr:link>.</fr:p>
 
   
   <fr:tree
toc="false"
numbered="true"
show-heading="true"
show-metadata="false"
expanded="true"
root="false"
xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>3742</fr:anchor><fr:addr>#378</fr:addr><fr:route>unstable-378.xml</fr:route><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon><fr:date><fr:year>2024</fr:year><fr:month>1</fr:month><fr:day>29</fr:day></fr:date><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link
type="local"
href="jonmsterling.xml"
addr="jonmsterling"
title="Jon Sterling">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:parent>jms-00MB</fr:parent></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
 <fr:p>We must show that for every equivalence class <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[u\in  A/E]]></fr:tex> there exists an element <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[a\in  A]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[q{\mathopen {}\left (a\right )\mathclose {}}=u]]></fr:tex>. By definition <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[u={\mathopen {}\left  [a\right  ]\mathclose {}}_{E}=q{\mathopen {}\left (a\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> for some <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[a\in  A]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
</fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree>
 
</fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree><fr:tree
