type="local"
href="jms-00M8.xml"
addr="jms-00M8"
title="Surjection">surjection</fr:link>.</fr:p>
 
   
   <fr:tree
toc="false"
numbered="true"
show-heading="true"
show-metadata="false"
expanded="true"
root="false"
xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>3753</fr:anchor><fr:addr>#376</fr:addr><fr:route>unstable-376.xml</fr:route><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon><fr:date><fr:year>2024</fr:year><fr:month>1</fr:month><fr:day>29</fr:day></fr:date><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link
type="local"
href="jonmsterling.xml"
addr="jonmsterling"
title="Jon Sterling">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:parent>jms-00MD</fr:parent></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
 <fr:p>For the <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00KI.xml"
addr="jms-00KI"
title="Closure of functions under identity and composition">identity function</fr:link> on a set <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex>, we must check that for all <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[a\in  A]]></fr:tex>, there exists an element <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[a'\in  A]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[a'=a]]></fr:tex>. Of course, we choose <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[a' := a]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>

 <fr:p>Let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f\colon  A\twoheadrightarrow  B]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[g\colon  B\twoheadrightarrow  C]]></fr:tex> be two <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00M8.xml"
addr="jms-00M8"
title="Surjection">surjections</fr:link>. To show that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[g\circ  f\colon  A\to  C]]></fr:tex> is a <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00M8.xml"
addr="jms-00M8"
title="Surjection">surjection</fr:link>, we fix <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[c\in  C]]></fr:tex> to exhibit some <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[a\in  A]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[g{\mathopen {}\left (f{\mathopen {}\left (a\right )\mathclose {}}\right )\mathclose {}} = c]]></fr:tex>. Because <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[g\colon  B\twoheadrightarrow  C]]></fr:tex> is <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00M8.xml"
addr="jms-00M8"
title="Surjection">surjective</fr:link>, there exists <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[b\in  B]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[g{\mathopen {}\left (b\right )\mathclose {}} = c]]></fr:tex>. Becuase <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f\colon  A\twoheadrightarrow  B]]></fr:tex> is <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00M8.xml"
addr="jms-00M8"
title="Surjection">surjective</fr:link>, there exists <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[a\in  A]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f{\mathopen {}\left (a\right )\mathclose {}} = b]]></fr:tex>. Thus we have <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[g{\mathopen {}\left (f{\mathopen {}\left (a\right )\mathclose {}}\right )\mathclose {}}=g{\mathopen {}\left (b\right )\mathclose {}}=c]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
</fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree>
 
</fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree><fr:tree
