xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>4333</fr:anchor><fr:addr>jms-00M7</fr:addr><fr:route>jms-00M7.xml</fr:route><fr:title>Logical characterisation of <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00KR.xml"
addr="jms-00KR"
title="Bijection">bijections</fr:link></fr:title><fr:taxon>Theorem</fr:taxon><fr:date><fr:year>2024</fr:year><fr:month>1</fr:month><fr:day>29</fr:day></fr:date><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link
type="local"
href="jonmsterling.xml"
addr="jonmsterling"
title="Jon Sterling">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author><fr:contributor><fr:link
type="local"
href="marcelofiore.xml"
addr="marcelofiore"
title="Marcelo Fiore">Marcelo Fiore</fr:link></fr:contributor></fr:authors></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>For a <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00KF.xml"
addr="jms-00KF"
title="Function">function</fr:link> <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f\colon  A\to  B]]></fr:tex>, the following are equivalent:</fr:p><fr:ol><fr:li>the <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00KF.xml"
addr="jms-00KF"
title="Function">function</fr:link> <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f\colon  A \to  B]]></fr:tex> is <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00KR.xml"
addr="jms-00KR"
title="Bijection">bijective</fr:link>;</fr:li>
 <fr:li>we have <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\forall  b\in  B\mathpunct {.} \exists ! a\in  A\mathpunct {.} f{\mathopen {}\left (a\right )\mathclose {}}=b]]></fr:tex>;</fr:li>
 <fr:li>we have both <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\forall  b\in  B\mathpunct {.} \exists  a\in  A\mathpunct {.} f{\mathopen {}\left (a\right )\mathclose {}}=b]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\forall  a_1,a_2\in  A\mathpunct {.} f{\mathopen {}\left (a_1\right )\mathclose {}}=f{\mathopen {}\left (a_2\right )\mathclose {}}\implies  a_1=a_2]]></fr:tex>.</fr:li></fr:ol>
 
   
   <fr:tree
toc="false"
numbered="true"
show-heading="true"
show-metadata="false"
expanded="true"
root="false"
xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>3721</fr:anchor><fr:addr>#381</fr:addr><fr:route>unstable-381.xml</fr:route><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon><fr:date><fr:year>2024</fr:year><fr:month>1</fr:month><fr:day>29</fr:day></fr:date><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link
type="local"
href="jonmsterling.xml"
addr="jonmsterling"
title="Jon Sterling">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:parent>jms-00M7</fr:parent></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
 <fr:p>We first prove that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f\colon  A\to  B]]></fr:tex> is <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00KR.xml"
addr="jms-00KR"
title="Bijection">bijective</fr:link> if and only if we have <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\forall  b\in  B\mathpunct {.} \exists ! a\in  A\mathpunct {.} f{\mathopen {}\left (a\right )\mathclose {}}=b]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
 <fr:ul><fr:li>Indeed, suppose that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex> is a <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00KR.xml"
addr="jms-00KR"
title="Bijection">bijection</fr:link> and fix <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[b\in  B]]></fr:tex> to check that there exists some unique <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[a\in  A]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f{\mathopen {}\left (a\right )\mathclose {}}=b]]></fr:tex>. We let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[a = f^{-1}{\mathopen {}\left (b\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> and we do indeed have <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f{\mathopen {}\left (a\right )\mathclose {}}=f{\mathopen {}\left (f^{-1}{\mathopen {}\left (b\right )\mathclose {}}\right )\mathclose {}}=b]]></fr:tex>; to see that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[a]]></fr:tex> is unique with this property, we fix <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[a_1,a_2\in  A]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f{\mathopen {}\left (a_1\right )\mathclose {}}=b]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f{\mathopen {}\left (a_2\right )\mathclose {}}=b]]></fr:tex>. We have <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[a_1=f^{-1}{\mathopen {}\left (f{\mathopen {}\left (a_1\right )\mathclose {}}\right )\mathclose {}}=f^{-1}{\mathopen {}\left (b\right )\mathclose {}}=f^{-1}{\mathopen {}\left (f{\mathopen {}\left (a_2\right )\mathclose {}}\right )\mathclose {}}=a_2]]></fr:tex>.</fr:li>
  <fr:li>Conversely, suppose that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\forall  b\in  B\mathpunct {.} \exists ! a\in  A\mathpunct {.} f{\mathopen {}\left (a\right )\mathclose {}}=b]]></fr:tex>; then we may define an inverse function <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f^{-1}\colon  B\to  A]]></fr:tex> sending <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[b\in  B]]></fr:tex> to the unique element <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[a\in  A]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f{\mathopen {}\left (a\right )\mathclose {}}=b]]></fr:tex>. We therefore have <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f{\mathopen {}\left (f^{-1}{\mathopen {}\left (b\right )\mathclose {}}\right )\mathclose {}}=b]]></fr:tex> by definition and <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f^{-1}{\mathopen {}\left (f{\mathopen {}\left (a\right )\mathclose {}}\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> is defined to be the unique element <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[a'\in  A]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f{\mathopen {}\left (a'\right )\mathclose {}} = f{\mathopen {}\left (a\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>; as <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[a']]></fr:tex> is assumed unique with this property and we clearly have <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f{\mathopen {}\left (a\right )\mathclose {}}=f{\mathopen {}\left (a\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>, we may conclude that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[a'=a]]></fr:tex> and so <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f^{-1}{\mathopen {}\left (f{\mathopen {}\left (a\right )\mathclose {}}\right )\mathclose {}}=a]]></fr:tex>.</fr:li></fr:ul>

 <fr:p>Next, we show that we have <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\forall  b\in  B\mathpunct {.} \exists ! a\in  A\mathpunct {.} f{\mathopen {}\left (a\right )\mathclose {}}=b]]></fr:tex> if and only if we have both <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\forall  b\in  B\mathpunct {.} \exists  a\in  A\mathpunct {.} f{\mathopen {}\left (a\right )\mathclose {}}=b]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\forall  a_1,a_2\in  A\mathpunct {.} f{\mathopen {}\left (a_1\right )\mathclose {}}=f{\mathopen {}\left (a_2\right )\mathclose {}}\implies  a_1=a_2]]></fr:tex>. In fact, this holds immediately by unfolding the definition of unique existence and the distribution of universal quantification over conjunction.</fr:p>
</fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree>
 
</fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree><fr:tree
