xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>4336</fr:anchor><fr:addr>jms-00M8</fr:addr><fr:route>jms-00M8.xml</fr:route><fr:title>Surjection</fr:title><fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon><fr:date><fr:year>2024</fr:year><fr:month>1</fr:month><fr:day>29</fr:day></fr:date><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link
type="local"
href="jonmsterling.xml"
addr="jonmsterling"
title="Jon Sterling">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author><fr:contributor><fr:link
type="local"
href="marcelofiore.xml"
addr="marcelofiore"
title="Marcelo Fiore">Marcelo Fiore</fr:link></fr:contributor></fr:authors></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>A function <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f\colon  A\to  B]]></fr:tex> is said to be <fr:em><fr:strong>surjective</fr:strong></fr:em> or a<fr:em><fr:strong>surjection</fr:strong></fr:em> when for we have <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\forall  b\in  B\mathpunct {.} \exists  a\in  A\mathpunct {.} f{\mathopen {}\left (a\right )\mathclose {}}=b]]></fr:tex>. A function satisfying this condition is written <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f\colon  A\twoheadrightarrow  B]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree><fr:tree
toc="true"
numbered="false"
show-heading="true"
show-metadata="true"
expanded="false"
root="false"
xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>4339</fr:anchor><fr:addr>jms-00KR</fr:addr><fr:route>jms-00KR.xml</fr:route><fr:title>Bijection</fr:title><fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon><fr:date><fr:year>2024</fr:year><fr:month>1</fr:month><fr:day>23</fr:day></fr:date><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link
type="local"
href="jonmsterling.xml"
addr="jonmsterling"
title="Jon Sterling">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author><fr:contributor><fr:link
type="local"
href="marcelofiore.xml"
addr="marcelofiore"
title="Marcelo Fiore">Marcelo Fiore</fr:link></fr:contributor></fr:authors></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>A <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00KF.xml"
addr="jms-00KF"
title="Function">function</fr:link> <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f\colon  A \to  B]]></fr:tex> is said to be <fr:em><fr:strong>bijective</fr:strong></fr:em> or <fr:em><fr:strong>bijection</fr:strong></fr:em> whenever there exists a (necessarily unique) function <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[g\colon  B\to  A]]></fr:tex> (referred to as the <fr:em><fr:strong>inverse</fr:strong></fr:em> of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex>) that is simultaneously a <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00KS.xml"
addr="jms-00KS"
title="Section-retraction pair">retraction</fr:link> and a <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00KS.xml"
addr="jms-00KS"
title="Section-retraction pair">section</fr:link> of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f\colon  A \to  B]]></fr:tex> in the sense that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[g\circ  f=\mathsf {id}_{A}]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f\circ  g = \mathsf {id}_{B}]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p><fr:p>We will often write <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f^{-1}\colon  B\to  A]]></fr:tex> for the inverse to a bijection <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f\colon  A \to  B]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
 
   
   <fr:tree
toc="false"
numbered="true"
show-heading="true"
show-metadata="false"
expanded="true"
root="false"
xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>3616</fr:anchor><fr:addr>#393</fr:addr><fr:route>unstable-393.xml</fr:route><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon><fr:date><fr:year>2024</fr:year><fr:month>1</fr:month><fr:day>23</fr:day></fr:date><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link
type="local"
href="jonmsterling.xml"
addr="jonmsterling"
title="Jon Sterling">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:parent>jms-00KR</fr:parent></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
 <fr:p>To see that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[g\colon  B\to  A]]></fr:tex> is unique, we fix any other <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[g']]></fr:tex> that is simultaneously a <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00KS.xml"
addr="jms-00KS"
title="Section-retraction pair">retraction</fr:link> and a <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00KS.xml"
addr="jms-00KS"
title="Section-retraction pair">section</fr:link> of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex> and show that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[g=g']]></fr:tex>:</fr:p>
 <fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[   \begin {aligned}     g &= \mathsf {id}_{A}\circ  g\\     &= {\mathopen {}\left (g'\circ  f\right )\mathclose {}} \circ  g\\     &= g'\circ {\mathopen {}\left (f\circ  g\right )\mathclose {}}\\     &= g'\circ \mathsf {id}_{B}\\     &= g'   \end {aligned}  ]]></fr:tex>
</fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree>
 
</fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree></fr:backmatter></fr:tree>